<p>
<strong>Wheeling-Pittsburgh Steel Corporation, headquartered in Wheeling,
West Virginia, is America's ninth largest integrated steel producer. 
The company is a wholly owned subsidiary of WHX Corporation, New York.
Wheeling-Pittsburgh operates steel producing and finishing facilities in 
13 states.  In 1995, the company produced 2.2 million tons of raw steel, 
shipped 2.5 million tons and sales for the year totaled $1.4 billion.  
Wheeling-Pittsburgh, which employs 5,400, was incorporated in 1920.
For additional information, please 
<a href="overview/contact-info.html">contact Wheeling-Pittsburgh
Steel Corporation</a>.
</p>

